14. PRIVACY POLICY:

14.1 General Information

This Privacy Policy, together with The entirety of the End-User License Agreement, applies to usage of The Application called “RouteWise”.

RouteWise, is an application developed by GLOBAL TRAFFIC ACCIDENT REDUCTION INC., an Ohio-based corporation operating as TNEDICCA® (herby referred to as The Company). TNEDICCA® is committed to protecting and respecting the privacy of users of The Application and The Content. This policy sets forth the basis on which any personal data that is collected from or provided by users will be stored, processed, and shared. Please read the following information carefully and thoroughly to understand The Company’s practices regarding personal data and its guidelines for use.

14.2 Types of Data Collected & Processed

The Company collects personal data specifically and voluntarily provided by users.

Personal data is defined as any information by which a user of The Application can be identified, such as names, usernames, email addresses, passwords, physical addresses, GPS coordinates, and phone number(s), as well as the make, model, year, and vehicle identification information associated with their account. The provision and collection of this information is necessary in order to allow The Application to function as described in the End-User License Agreement. Such personal data is requested of users when they create an account within The Application.

To provide services associated with The Application, The Company needs to collect geographical location data from any functioning mobile device sensors, continuously and consistently, every few seconds regardless of whether The Application is in-use. For The Application to function properly, it requires that GPS technology and location services be enabled. Furthermore, the mobile device must grant The Application permission to access these functionalities in order to determine current location. By downloading and using The Application, users consent to their data being collected and used for such purposes. Providing The Application services also requires that data be collected in regard to driving styles and habits collectively referred to as “Driving Behaviors”.

The Company also collects technical information, including—but not limited to—the type of mobile device in use, the mobile operating system, and current time zone settings. However, TNEDICCA® will not collect or process sensitive data, which is to be understood of personal data that is capable of revealing a user’s race or ethnicity; religious, philosophical and other type of beliefs; political opinions; trade union associations; or personal data capable of revealing a user’s state of health or sexual orientation.

14.3 Data Processing

All personal data voluntarily provided by users will be processed by automated means using proprietary software that correlates with The Application and its related services. It should be noted that the personal data requested from users when they register to use The Application is necessary to enable use.

14.4 Disclosure of User Data

For the purpose of providing the intended services, The Company may disclose some or all of its collected data. Such information may be provided to partners of The Company for processing, which will allow them to (1) improve The Application’s user experience and (2) generate marketing communications for those users who have opted-in to such correspondence. By downloading and using The Application, users also agree that The Company may disclose personal data to certain third parties not referred to in this privacy policy, such cases would include: 

If The Company buys or sells—or proposes to buy or sell—any part of the business or its individual assets; in which case the relevant data controller may disclose users’ personal data to the prospective seller or buyer.
If TNEDICCA®, or subsequently all of The Company’s assets, are acquired by a third party or it is proposed that The Company will be acquired; in which case personal data held by TNEDICCA® could be one of the transferred assets.
If The Company is under a legal duty to disclose or share such data in order to comply with legal or regulatory obligations or requests.

14.5 Personal Data Access

Personal data provided to TNEDICCA® during use of The Application may be accessed by staff members or one of its suppliers in charge of processing data. However, TNEDICCA® will act to ensure that such access is limited only to those individuals who require it for the outlined services and/or for the purposes set forth in this document.

14.6 Personal Data Storage

Any data collected by The Company may be transferred to and/or stored at a location outside the United States. Staffs operating outside this jurisdiction who work for The Company or one of its affiliates and/or partners may also process it. By submitting personal data, users agree to such transfer, storing, and processing needs. TNEDICCA® will take all reasonable steps to ensure this data is treated securely and in accordance with all aforementioned portions of this privacy policy.

14.7 Length of Personal Account Data Storage 

Personal account data provided to The Company will be retained for the duration of use and for a period of one year after, in order to allow usage at a later time. After one year of nonuse, the user’s driving behavior and location-based data is anonymized to de-associate it from their account and all personal account information (such as username and password) is deleted. If a user deletes their profile within The Application, all personal account data will be deleted immediately.

14.8 Changes & Alterations

The Company reserves the right to change this privacy policy at any given time. All changes will be posted to this page and, where appropriate, be delivered as a notification to users via e-mail or when users are asked to read and accept these changes in order to continue use of The Application and The Content.

14.9 Tailored Marketing Communications 

The core functions of The Application and The Content are (1) the analysis of data provided by users for profiling purposes such as determining route ratings, individual preferences, driving habits, and consumption needs, and (2) the processing of this data to aggregate statistics, draft models, measure consumer habits, and/or other driving-related statistics. 

Such methods are used to assess individual scores and, more specifically, allow partners of The Company to propose commercial offers to users. By completing the sign-up process, installing The Application, and engaging with The Content, users agree that they provide their explicit consent to (1) the collecting, storing and processing of all relevant data and behavior statistics for profiling purposes, and (2) the sharing of this data for the use and delivery of personalized marketing offers, which will be delivered to users via their preferred method of contact. TNEDICCA® may receive compensation for sharing such data. 

It should be noted that when following any of the outside links provided by partners of the Company, it is understood that these websites and any other services contained within have their own privacy policies and TNEDICCA® does not accept any responsibility or liability for any personal data that may be collected, such as contact and location data. Users should check their accompanying privacy policies prior to submitting any personal data. 

Users also give consent to allow TNEDICCA® the right to contact them on an as-needed basis via their preferred method of communication (i.e. text, phone or e-mail) with regard to account maintenance, user experience, inquiries, accessibility issues, etc.

Users can withdraw their consent to allowing their data to be used for profiling purposes or to receiving further marketing communications, at any time and free of charge, by deleting The Application from their device(s) or by contacting TNEDICCA® at info@tnedicca.com.

14.10 Contact Information

For any information or request on the protection of personal data, please contact us at info@tnedicca.com.

By accepting these terms and conditions, I acknowledge that I have carefully read the Privacy policy and:

I voluntarily give my informed consent to the collection, storage and processing of my location and personal driving data, and trip information to TNEDICCA® for profiling purposes such as collecting aggregated statistics, optimizing routes, designing new traffic models, etc.

I give my informed consent to the processing and sharing of my personal data by TNEDICCA® and its partners (as defined within the privacy policy), which may include—but is not limited to—partners located within and/or outside the US, for the purpose of enhancing user experience and developing new capabilities.
I understand that any incurred charges presented as a result of usage will be my sole financial responsibility.

I understand and agree that all suggested routes are generally estimated to have lower crash risk than their alternatives. However, road hazards and auto accidents can cause difference in potential outcomes. I expressly acknowledge that neither TNEDICCA® nor The Application are liable for any such incidents that occur as a result of using The Application.
